    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Rear View Mirrors</title>
        <para>The driver side exterior rear view mirrors are located forward of the driver side window and are mounted
            on break-away brackets. The mirror is a dual head mirror with an adjustable convex and rear view flat
            section.
        </para>
        <figure id="f4700628" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g4700628.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 28. Rear View Mirror (Driver Side)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. DRIVER SIDE REAR VIEW MIRROR ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>2. OPTIONAL HARNESS CONNECTION FOR HEATED MIRROR</callout1>
                <callout1>3. MIRROR MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>4. DRIVER SIDE ASSIST GRAB HANDLE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>The passenger side mounted rear view mirror assembly is mounted on a break-away bracket forward of the
            entrance door with both convex and flat mirror heads. The mirror is situated forward of the bus body
            structure to allow for maximum visibility by the driver.
        </para>
        <figure id="f4700629" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g4700629.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 29. Rear View Mirror (Passenger Side)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. PASSENGER SIDE REAR VIEW MIRROR MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>2. PASSENGER SIDE REAR VIEW MIRROR HEAD ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>3. VANDAL LOCK</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcsubproc>
